@{b}BREAK@{ub}

Usage: @{b}BREAK@{ub}

The BREAK instruction is used to exit from the range of a @{"DO" LINK "DO/main"} instruction or
from within an @{"INTERPRET" LINK "INTERPRET/main"}ed string, and is valid only in these contexts. If used
within a DO statement, BREAK exits from the innermost DO statement containing
the BREAK. This contrasts with the otherwise similar @{"LEAVE" LINK "LEAVE/main"} instruction, which
exits only from an iterative DO}.

Example:
@{fg shine}
        do                            /* begin block          */

            if (i > 3) then break     /* all done?            */

            a = a + 1

            y.a = name

        end                           /* end block            */
@{fg text}
